article_title: U.S. Jobless Claims Remain at Historically Low Levels
article_text:
WASHINGTON—The number of Americans seeking first-time unemployment benefits rose last week but remained at historically low levels that are consistent with job growth.

Initial jobless claims increased by 14,000 to a seasonally adjusted 281,000 in the week ended April 4, the Labor Department said Thursday. Economists surveyed by The Wall Street...
